The paper discusses the logical connectives and their short-circuit behavior, which is related to logic and semantics. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of path-satisfiability, which is related to programming languages and software engineering, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the theoretical understanding of Short Circuit Logic, which is related to formal languages and automata, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of programming and program execution, which is related to computer systems and control, making cs.SC (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
